iously announced that he will embark on <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-gallagher-oasis-definitely-maybe-30th-anniversary-uk-tour-dates-tickets-3515369">a tour of the UK and Ireland next summer</a> to celebrate the 30th anniversary of the band&#39;s 1994 debut album.</p><p> It appears that ex-Oasis guitarist Bonehead will be joining him on the tour following his solo projects and previous cancer scare – <a href="https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/music/oasis-bonehead-on-recent-cancer-diagnosis-its-all-clear-its-gone-3320076">he&#39;s since been given the all-clear</a> . However, Liam later stated said that brother and former-bandmate <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-gallagher-says-noel-gallagher-turned-down-definitely-maybe-tour-3516455">Noel Gallagher turned down the offer to take part in the upcoming dates.</a></p><p> Although not taking part in the tour, Noel <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/noel-gallagher-confirms-definitely-maybe-30th-anniversary-reissue-for-2024-denies-oasis-reunion-tour-3436441">did confirm plans for a 30th anniversary reissue of the seminal album</a> to mark the occasion.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-gallagher-teases-joint-album-with-john-squire-as-the-best-record-since-the-beatles-revolver-3520505">Liam Gallagher teases joint album with John Squire as “the best record since The Beatles&#39; &#39;Revolver&#39;”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
